The paper discusses reinforcement learning and visual imitation learning using recurrent Siamese networks. The primary focus is on using these networks to provide a reward signal to an RL agent, which falls under the category of reinforcement learning (cs.LG). The paper also heavily relies on computer vision techniques such as image encoding and distance computation, which suggests that it could also fall under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of multi-task data and temporal consistency, which are both topics that fall under the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and robotics (cs.RO). Finally, the paper discusses the use of humanoid agents, which suggests that it could also fall under the category of systems and control (cs.SY).
